thread.title: UFC 192 fight card

author: MARK LA MONICA
title: UFC 192 fight card
text:
Johny Hendricks was pulled from Saturday's UFC 192 welterweight fight against Tyron Woodley because of weight-cut issues, the UFC announced Friday.
The rest of the UFC 192 fight card remains intact with 12 bouts heading into Friday afternoon's weigh-ins. Joseph Benavidez vs. Ali Bagautinov was elevated from the Fox Sports 1 prelims to the pay-per-view portion of the card.
Latest MMA stories Weidman helps gym member fight cancer Jon Jones avoids jail in plea deal UFC sues to end state's ban on MMA bouts UFC schedules event at The Garden UFC Fight Night Japan fight card Daniel Cormier makes his first defense of the UFC light heavyweight title at UFC 192 this Saturday against Alexander Gustafsson.
UFC 192 takes place at the Toyota Center in Houston, Texas. Here's a look at the latest fight card:
